
rpdf extracts text and layout from PDF documents, using pdftohtml and
OCRopus.

version 0.2 (2010-04-04)

---------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALLATION
---------------------------------------------------------------------

rpdf requires slightly modified versions of specifc OCRopus and
pdftohtml releases, which are included, as well as ghostscript. To
install OCRopus and pdftohtml, follow the instructions in the
respective sub-directories.

[Simpler or more detailed installation instructions may follow at some
point.]

---------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
---------------------------------------------------------------------

rpdf [-d int] [-p int] file.pdf

 -d int : debug level
 -p int : max. number of pages to parse

If -p is not specified, what happens depends on whether rpdf can use
pdftohtml or has to fall back on OCR. With pdftohtml, it will parse
all; with OCRopus it will parse 1-3 pages depending on the length of
the pdf document. (OCRopus is slow: expect 10-20 seconds per page.)

